From ed330fe16245529afe65c22e86a7f99d27734ea8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ian <ian@wafer.ai>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 2026 07:02:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] fix: decide Q dtype at allocation time based on batch
 size
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Avoids redundant bf16→fp8 cast when Triton decode falls through to ASM
path for large batches. The batch size is known at q_out allocation time
(q_nope.shape[0]), so we can pick the correct dtype up front.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
